def: A name applied to various skin diseases, but especially toringworm. See Ringworm, and Sycosis.
One who, or that which, produces reverberation.
Behind the stomach; -- said of two lobes of the carapace ofcertain crustaceans.
Without; deprived or destitute of. Rarely used as an Englishword. "Sans fail." Chaucer.Sans teeth, sans eyes, sans taste, sans everything. Shak.
Having four seeds. Tetraspermous plant, a plant which producesfour seeds in each flower.
In England, an ecclesiastical dignitary, next in rank below abishop, whom he assists, and by whom he is appointed, though withindependent authority. Blackstone.
A division of Radiolaria; -- called also Monocyttaria.-- Mon`o*zo"ic, a.
